column5: I'd pick George to KO Chuck Norris I just watched the fight of GSP and Matt Serra, wow... he was so focused.
That fight defines the work domination.

a great card tonight... wow... talk about bloody!.... I feel for the guy from BC though.. what a wimp.... I have NEVER seen anyone backpeddle as much.... even the announcers mentioned I am not too sure what his strategy is here... LOL I was howling..   I would still take Lew vs. Chuck Norris though.... my thinking is a fist would smash you from his Moustache before you stood up!  G
I enjoyed the kid who fought from WoodBridge..  He took a beating but kept on coming for more.
Ya that Woodbridge kid was beaten like a redheaded stepchild!!! ... but it was unreal he didn't give up after those knees to the face!!! real testament to Canadian toughness!!
I agree GSP is a great fighter but Chuck Norris? Come on now do we have to bring back the old Chuck Norris thread

Funniest fight I have ever seen..... even the ref stated... Iam not sure what his strategy is here! it was the saddest fight I have seen in a long time

What was up with that guy running away?  Now that I remember that guy had a history of flinching, giving up or just plain being a wussy (as far as UFC goes).  How that guy keeps making it on the main events is beyond me.  Did I miss something?  Was the guy hurt or rigged with some sort of nuclear device that would blow if he got hit?  forrest

OK.  A friend of a friends sisters guy cousin just confirmed this:  Story behind Kalib Starnes running away:  Al-Quida placed a nuclear device in his jock and body sensors all over him.  If one of those sensors got hit, BLAMO!!!  Kalib is a hero!!!!
How 'bout, Chuck Norris vs Bruce Lee?
Gerritt that was hilarious. what made it even funnier was watching Your avatar up in the corner showing him what he was suppose to be doing............. LOL!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!   Dann

Overall, I'd have to say UFC 83 was pretty disappointing compared to previous shows.  I didn't get the flashy victory that I was so hoping for in the main event Travis Lutter ran out of gas Starnes ran out of courage  Everything else was everything else
